      "comment": "JESSICAS STORY (1) is working to towards a win having finished progressively closer to the winner with each of her past five starts. Made it back-to-back placings when she came from this barrier and battled on bravely for a 2.8m second at this venue. Big chance to go one better. LITTLE TEDEY (8) came from this barrier when he scored at Melton three starts ago and drew there again last time out when third at Kilmore, beaten 1.4 metres. Shouldn't spend a penny in the run and the sprint lane may come in handy. Big chance. ROBERT JOHN (5) will be nearing peak fitness and is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish third at Terang. MADGE EGAN (2) is in the mix aided by a good draw.",
